Feature: GCSE English Training Example Synthesis
  As a machine learning engineer
  I want to generate GCSE English tutoring training examples via Claude API synthesis
  So that I can produce a Phase 1 baseline dataset for fine-tuning Nemotron 3 Nano

  Background:
    Given the generation plan is loaded from "domains/gcse-english-tutor/generation-plan.yaml"
    And the system prompt is the standard GCSE English tutor prompt
    And the Claude API is available and configured

  # ━━ GROUP A: Key Examples ━━

  # Why: Core generation path — a single reasoning example with think block is the primary output type
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Generating a single-turn reasoning example
    Given a generation target for "macbeth" with topic "character_analysis" and grade target 7
    And the target layer is "behaviour" and type is "reasoning"
    When the synthesis script generates an example
    Then the output should contain a system message with the standard tutor prompt
    And the output should contain a user message with a realistic student question
    And the assistant message should contain a think block followed by a visible response
    And the metadata should include the correct text, topic, grade target, layer, type, and source

  # Why: Direct mode examples are the second format — no think block
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Generating a direct (non-reasoning) example
    Given a generation target for "an_inspector_calls" with topic "factual_recall" and type "direct"
    And the target layer is "knowledge"
    When the synthesis script generates an example
    Then the assistant message should not contain a think block
    And the metadata type should be "direct"

  # Why: Multi-turn essay feedback is a distinct prompt template with 3+ turns
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Multi-turn examples contain at least 4 messages after system message
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Generating a multi-turn essay feedback example
    Given a generation target for "a_christmas_carol" with topic "essay_feedback" and type "reasoning"
    When the synthesis script generates a multi-turn example
    Then the output should contain at least 4 user and assistant messages after the system message
    And each assistant message should contain a think block
    And the conversation should show progressive scaffolding of the student's understanding

  # Why: Layer routing is the critical architectural decision — behaviour goes to train, knowledge to RAG
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Routing behaviour examples to the training file
    Given a generated example with layer "behaviour"
    When the output is written
    Then the example should be appended to "output/train.jsonl"
    And the example should not appear in "output/rag_index/knowledge.jsonl"

  # Why: Knowledge layer routing to RAG index
  @key-example
  Scenario: Routing knowledge examples to the RAG index
    Given a generated example with layer "knowledge"
    When the output is written
    Then the example should be appended to "output/rag_index/knowledge.jsonl"
    And the example should not appear in "output/train.jsonl"

  # Why: The generation plan drives the entire synthesis — it must be read correctly
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Processing all targets from the generation plan
    Given a generation plan with 10 targets
    When the synthesis script runs to completion
    Then all 10 targets should be attempted
    And the progress log should report the total count attempted

  # Why: Invalid API responses must not corrupt the training set
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Rejecting a malformed API response
    Given the Claude API returns a response that does not match the expected JSON schema
    When the validator checks the response
    Then the response should be written to "output/rejected.jsonl" with a reason code
    And the response should not be written to "output/train.jsonl" or "output/rag_index/knowledge.jsonl"

  # ━━ GROUP B: Boundary Conditions ━━

  # Why: The 75/25 split is a hard constraint for Nemotron 3 Nano MoE — must be enforced as generation proceeds
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Acceptable split tolerance is +/-5% (70-80% reasoning, 20-30% direct)
  @boundary @smoke
  Scenario: Maintaining the 75/25 reasoning-to-direct split
    Given the generation plan produces targets that would result in 75% reasoning and 25% direct examples
    When the synthesis script processes all targets
    Then the accepted output should contain approximately 75% reasoning examples
    And the accepted output should contain approximately 25% direct examples

  # Why: Just-inside boundary — at exactly 75/25
  @boundary
  Scenario Outline: Split ratio within acceptable tolerance
    Given <total> accepted examples with <reasoning_count> reasoning and <direct_count> direct
    When the split ratio is calculated
    Then the ratio should be considered valid

    Examples:
      | total | reasoning_count | direct_count |
      | 100   | 75              | 25           |
      | 200   | 150             | 50           |
      | 300   | 225             | 75           |

  # Why: Just-outside boundary — ratio drift beyond tolerance should trigger a warning
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Split tolerance is +/-5%
  @boundary @negative
  Scenario: Split ratio drifting beyond acceptable tolerance
    Given 100 accepted examples with 85 reasoning and 15 direct
    When the split ratio is calculated
    Then a warning should be logged that the ratio has drifted from the 75/25 target

  # Why: Generation plan may have zero entries — script should handle gracefully
  @boundary
  Scenario: Generation plan with zero targets
    Given a generation plan with 0 targets
    When the synthesis script runs
    Then no output files should be created
    And the progress log should report 0 targets attempted

  # Why: Single target is the minimum useful plan
  @boundary
  Scenario: Generation plan with exactly one target
    Given a generation plan with 1 target
    When the synthesis script runs to completion
    Then exactly 1 example should be generated (accepted or rejected)

  # Why: Metadata grade_target can be null for non-graded content — must be handled
  @boundary
  Scenario: Generating an example with null grade target
    Given a generation target with grade_target set to null
    When the synthesis script generates an example
    Then the metadata grade_target should be null in the output
    And the example should still pass validation

  # ━━ GROUP C: Negative Cases ━━

  # Why: Missing generation plan should fail fast, not generate nothing silently
  @negative
  Scenario: Generation plan file does not exist
    Given the generation plan file "domains/gcse-english-tutor/generation-plan.yaml" is missing
