  # Why: API failure should not crash the pipeline — fail gracefully and continue
  @negative
  Scenario: Claude API returns an error for a single target
    Given a generation plan with 5 targets
    And the Claude API returns an error for target 3
    When the synthesis script processes all targets
    Then targets 1, 2, 4, and 5 should be processed normally
    And target 3 should be recorded in "output/rejected.jsonl" with the API error reason
    And the progress log should report 1 rejection

  # Why: Metadata with invalid values should be caught by validation
  @negative
  Scenario: Generated example has invalid metadata field values
    Given a generated example where the "text" metadata field contains an unrecognised value
    When the validator checks the example
