  @edge-case
  Scenario: Output files remain valid after interrupted write
    Given the synthesis script is writing an accepted example to "output/train.jsonl"
    And the script is interrupted mid-write
    When the output file is inspected
    Then every complete line in the file should be valid JSON
    And no partial JSON line should be present

  # Why: Retrying the same target should not produce exact duplicates in output
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Duplicate content is detected on retry
    Given a generation target that was previously attempted and rejected
    When the synthesis script retries the same target
    And the API returns content identical to an already-accepted example
    Then the duplicate should be written to "output/rejected.jsonl" with reason "duplicate"

  # ━━ EDGE CASE EXPANSION: Integration Boundaries ━━

  # Why: Claude API rate limits (429) should trigger backoff, not permanent rejection
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Maximum 3 retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Handling Claude API rate limiting with retry
    Given a generation plan with 5 targets
    And the Claude API returns a rate limit error for target 2
